 "approach_html": "<strong> Approach:</strong>  Best approached from Wasdale where there are a couple of big car parks. Allow an hour to hike uphill to the crag. The route Leads most of the way to Scarfell Pike, but once the Scarfell Crag comes into sight, take a right less used fork in the path to the crag. Access to the starting terrace is gained via a path on the right of the crag.<br><br><strong>Descent:</strong> There are multiple options for decent on each end of the crag and require steep scrambling and/or and abseil. <br>",
